Lock-less list, the first concurrency TU. Per rule 0017: the LKMM
primitives (smp_load_acquire, READ_ONCE, try_cmpxchg incl. its
update-old-on-failure contract) stay compiled in C as per-primitive,
per-operand shims in rust/helpers/llist.c; only control flow is
translated. Ordering is NOT reimplemented in Rust — kernel::sync::atomic
lift is a separate, human-reviewed future step.

Validated: full regression boot green; note the boot itself exercises
llist (vmalloc deferred-free, workqueue paths), so this is live runtime
validation, not just suites. Symbols verified from llist_rs.o.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
